events.body:
@wip-abramson: There are 4 commits now. For some help on squashing commits see https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#squashing-commits or page 284 of the Pro Git [book](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2). You also have a merge commit that you'll want to remove. 

If you'd rather start afresh on your branch and go back to latest top commit on master you can do a `git reset -hard insert_current_top_commit_hash`, re-add your commit and force push.

edit: It is also recommended that you open a PR from a[ topic branch](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#contributor-workflow) rather than the master branch in your fork.
